# Frontend Extension Module

## PURPOSE
Contains all client-side extension code that runs in the browser.
Handles UI, email scanning, authentication, and communication with backend API.

## STRUCTURE
- /core: Platform-agnostic business logic
- /providers: Email provider implementations (Gmail, Outlook, Yahoo)
- /ui: User interface components and pages
- /background: Service worker for background tasks
- /api: Client-side API communication layer

## RESPONSIBILITIES
- Scan user's email inbox for subscriptions
- Display subscriptions with unsubscribe links
- Handle user authentication flow
- Enforce free tier limits (5 subs) before payment
- Communicate with backend for user/payment data
- Cross-browser compatibility

## REFERENCES
- Parent: /.windsurf (root context)
- Modules: /src/core/.windsurf, /src/providers/.windsurf, /src/ui/.windsurf

## RULES
- Keep code browser-agnostic (use WebExtension APIs)
- No hardcoded API keys or secrets
- All provider implementations must follow same interface
- UI must be responsive and accessible
